    <entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>Rust traits: shared behavior</title>
        <published>2026-07-01T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2026-07-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        <author>
          <name>Unknown</name>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://rustynotes.com/all-posts/rust-traits/" type="text/html"/>
        <id>https://rustynotes.com/all-posts/rust-traits/</id>
        
        <content type="html">&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;eng-rust-traits-shared-behavior&quot;&gt;(&lt;em&gt;Eng&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;) Rust traits: shared behavior&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Traits define shared behavior across types. A trait declares methods that implementing types must provide. Other languages call this an interface. Rust&#x27;s twist: traits can also provide default method implementations.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Traits let you write generic code over any type that implements a behavior.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;defining-a-trait&quot;&gt;Defining a trait&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;rust&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#2b303b;color:#c0c5ce;&quot; class=&quot;language-rust &quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-rust&quot; data-lang=&quot;rust&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;trait &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Summary {
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;fn &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#8fa1b3;&quot;&gt;summarize&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;self&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;) -&amp;gt; String;
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;fn &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#8fa1b3;&quot;&gt;preview&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;self&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;) -&amp;gt; String {
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;        format!(&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#a3be8c;&quot;&gt;Preview: &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#d08770;&quot;&gt;{}&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;quot;, &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;self&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#96b5b4;&quot;&gt;summarize&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;())
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    }
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Types that implement &lt;code&gt;Summary&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; must provide &lt;code&gt;summarize&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;. They get &lt;code&gt;preview&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; for free unless they override it.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;implementing-a-trait&quot;&gt;Implementing a trait&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;rust&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#2b303b;color:#c0c5ce;&quot; class=&quot;language-rust &quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-rust&quot; data-lang=&quot;rust&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;struct &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Article {
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;title&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: String,
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;body&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: String,
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;impl &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Summary &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;for &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Article {
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;fn &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#8fa1b3;&quot;&gt;summarize&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;self&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;) -&amp;gt; String {
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;        format!(&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#d08770;&quot;&gt;{}&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;quot;, &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;self&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.title)
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    }
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;rust&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#2b303b;color:#c0c5ce;&quot; class=&quot;language-rust &quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-rust&quot; data-lang=&quot;rust&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;let&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; article = Article { title: String::from(&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#a3be8c;&quot;&gt;Rust traps&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;quot;), body: String::from(&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#a3be8c;&quot;&gt;...&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;quot;) };
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;println!(&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#d08770;&quot;&gt;{}&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;quot;, article.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#96b5b4;&quot;&gt;summarize&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;());
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;println!(&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#d08770;&quot;&gt;{}&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;quot;, article.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#96b5b4;&quot;&gt;preview&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;());
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;using-traits-as-bounds&quot;&gt;Using traits as bounds&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generics accept trait bounds to constrain types.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th style=&quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt;Pattern&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;th style=&quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt;Meaning&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;&lt;&#x2F;thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;T: Summary&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;T&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; implements &lt;code&gt;Summary&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;fn notify&amp;lt;T: Summary&amp;gt;(item: &amp;amp;T)&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt;generic over any &lt;code&gt;Summary&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; type&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;impl Summary for MyType&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt;concrete implementation&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;tbody&gt;&lt;&#x2F;table&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;rust&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#2b303b;color:#c0c5ce;&quot; class=&quot;language-rust &quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-rust&quot; data-lang=&quot;rust&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;fn &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#8fa1b3;&quot;&gt;notify&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;item&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: &amp;amp;impl Summary) {
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    println!(&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#a3be8c;&quot;&gt;Breaking: &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#d08770;&quot;&gt;{}&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;quot;, item.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#96b5b4;&quot;&gt;summarize&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;());
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;impl Trait&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; syntax is shorthand for a generic bound. It reads naturally: &lt;code&gt;item&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; is some type that implements &lt;code&gt;Summary&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;default-implementations-reduce-duplication&quot;&gt;Default implementations reduce duplication&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When many types share the same logic, put it in the trait body.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;rust&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#2b303b;color:#c0c5ce;&quot; class=&quot;language-rust &quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-rust&quot; data-lang=&quot;rust&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;trait &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Summary {
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#b48ead;&quot;&gt;fn &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#8fa1b3;&quot;&gt;summarize&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;self&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;) -&amp;gt; String {
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;        String::from(&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#a3be8c;&quot;&gt;(no summary)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;quot;)
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;    }
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Callers still override when needed, but boilerplate disappears.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;difference-from-c-concepts-or-java-interfaces&quot;&gt;Difference from C++ concepts or Java interfaces&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Traits can provide defaults directly, not just declarations.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trait bounds are part of the type system, not a separate annotation layer.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A type can implement a trait only if either the trait or the type is local to your crate. This prevents orphan conflicts.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Core lesson: traits are Rust&#x27;s main abstraction for polymorphism. They separate &amp;quot;what a type can do&amp;quot; from &amp;quot;what a type is.&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
</content>
        
